    {
        "content": "<p>I know that <code>a &lt; p</code> is not always true, but I can always pick a <code>k</code> large enough that <code>a &lt; k * p</code></p>",
        "id": 484329205,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Kurkiewicz",
        "timestamp": 1732548124
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it's a common trick in elementary number theory, to use the fact that (p - 1)/2 factorial squared is equal to -1 mod p when p - 1 is divisible by 4.</p>",
        "id": 484329577,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Kurkiewicz",
        "timestamp": 1732548229
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I need it specifically for IMO 2008 N6 shortlist problem, which gives a weak bound on largest prime divisors of $n^2 + 1$:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.imo-official.org/problems/IMO2008SL.pdf\">https://www.imo-official.org/problems/IMO2008SL.pdf</a></p>",
        "id": 484330500,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Kurkiewicz",
        "timestamp": 1732548429
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Nat.cast_sub#doc\">docs#Nat.cast_sub</a></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ZMod_cast_sub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a_lt_p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">@</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ZMod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Semiring</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">toNatCast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cast_sub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a_lt_p</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">le</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
